\033[38;2;59;66;97m┃\033[0m\033[38;2;86;95;137m The words Socialism and Communism have the same meaning. They indicate a condition of society in which the wealth of the community: the land and the means of production, distribution and transport are held in common, production being for use and not for profit.\033[0m\\n- Sylvia Pankhurst, Future Society (1923)\n
