\033[38;2;59;66;97m┃\033[0m\033[38;2;86;95;137m A revolution is not a dinner party, or writing an essay, or painting a picture, or doing embroidery; it cannot be so refined, so leisurely and gentle, so temperate, kind, courteous, restrained and magnanimous. A revolution is an insurrection, an act of violence by which one class overthrows another.\033[0m\\n- Mao Zedong, Report on an Investigation of the Peasant Movement in Hunan (1927)\n
