\033[38;2;59;66;97m┃\033[0m\033[38;2;86;95;137m We should therefore see ourselves as in need of change and capable of being changed. We should not look upon ourselves as immutable, perfect and sacrosanct, as persons who need not and cannot be changed. When we pose the task of remoulding ourselves in social struggle, we are not demeaning ourselves; the objective laws of social development demand it. Unless we do so, we cannot make progress, or fulfill the task of changing society.\033[0m\\n- Liu Shaoqi, How to be a Good Communist (1939)\n
